      • testListIteratorPreviousAndHasPrevious

        public void testListIteratorPreviousAndHasPrevious()
        Test listIterator previous and hasPrevious
        Pre-Condition:
        List l initialized, 5 objects added to the list, object o added to the list l in last position, l listIterator initialized, otherList initialized
        Post-Condition:
        List l copied into otherList backwards
        Test cases:
        The test calls next until hasNext is false, then it adds the elements returned by previous to otherList until hasPrevious is false. OtherList should therefore now contain the same elements of l but in reverse order. This is tested by checking that the two lists have the same size and the object o is present in otherList in the first position.
